EC2 instance on AWS, there’s a wide range of real-world tasks you can practice — from basic Linux admin to full-stack app deployment. Here's a structured breakdown:
________________________________________
🔰 1. Basic Linux & Server Practice
•	✅ SSH into the instance.
•	🧱 Understand the Linux file system (ls, cd, mkdir, touch, nano, vim, etc.)
•	🧰 Install packages with apt (Ubuntu) or yum (Amazon Linux).
•	👤 Create and manage users and permissions.
•	📁 Upload and download files using scp or sftp.
________________________________________
🌐 2. Web Server Setup
•	🌍 Install and configure a web server:
o	NGINX (sudo apt install nginx)
o	Apache (sudo apt install apache2)
•	🔁 Create a static website and host it from /var/www/html.
•	🔒 Configure firewalls and allow traffic through security groups (port 80/443).
________________________________________
📜 3. Deploy Applications
•	🐍 Host a Python Flask app.
•	☕ Host a Java Spring Boot app.
•	⚙️ Host a Node.js Express app.
•	🗃️ Connect your app to a database (MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB).
________________________________________
🛠️ 4. DevOps & Automation Practice
•	🐳 Install and run Docker containers.
•	📦 Set up CI/CD with GitHub and deploy from push.
•	🧾 Write shell scripts for automation.
•	🧵 Use crontab for scheduling jobs.
________________________________________
🔐 5. Security & Network Practice
•	🔐 Configure firewall (ufw) or iptables.
•	🧪 Create and use different key pairs.
•	🌐 Practice VPC, Subnets, and NAT setup.
•	📡 Configure a domain name with Route 53.
•	🔒 Set up SSL with Let's Encrypt (Certbot).
________________________________________
🗃️ 6. File Storage & Backup
•	📁 Mount EBS volumes, format and use them.
•	📦 Create S3 buckets and sync files using aws s3 cp.
•	🔁 Automate EC2 to S3 backup using scripts.
________________________________________
📊 7. Monitoring & Logging
•	📈 Install CloudWatch Agent to push logs and metrics.
•	🔍 View logs from /var/log (e.g., syslog, auth.log).
•	📊 Set up basic alerting or metric dashboards.
________________________________________
🧪 8. Advanced Practice (Optional)
•	🕸️ Deploy a reverse proxy with NGINX for multiple apps.
•	🧬 Set up a private Git server or Jenkins CI.
•	🕵️ Install and configure fail2ban or auditd for security.
•	🚀 Deploy a Kubernetes cluster using kubeadm or kind.
________________________________________
💡 Pro Tip: Always remember to stop or terminate your instance when done — to avoid charges!

